ft class=m><span class=title> Re: Post 50 Pally and fa/fd question</span><hr size=1> The FD is much better for big targets because of resists.  Most of the velious weapons are 2 handers anyways and they do have competitive damage/delay ratios but don't have the resists(good for dragons/gods/etc) or the str, wis, hp, mana boosts.   Keep leveling up.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urement.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rement</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/01 11:19:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2922.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.3-cities.com/home/abdunn/public_html/werewolf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Post 50 Pally and fa/fd question</span><hr size=1> Just ask yourself, do you want to &quot;wait&quot; for the FD? Or can you live without it. Staying at 52 is fine, going ahead is fine, just ask yourself weather you really want it or not <p>Rement Soulblade<br>51st High Elf Cavalier<br>Guardians of Honor<br>Test Server </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utalenvorruglia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talenvor Ruglia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 186<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/01 4:01:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2922.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Post 50 Pally and fa/fd question</span><hr size=1> I'd say unless you are close to finishing FD, then it isn't worth it.  With the ac 40 + stats shield in fear now, and the new Plane of Air pal only quest sword 20/26 +15 wis 1h slash, it blows away the FD in my mind.  A kick butt one hander/shield combo.  Isn't that what we have always wanted ever since the FA was originally made? =)  Now if only we could convince Verant to give us a flaming shield... <p>Talenvor Ruglia<br>~Companions of the Gate~<br>60 Paladin </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utramddarkluxdeorum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tramddark Luxdeorum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 264<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/01 8:40:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2922.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Post 50 Pally and fa/fd question</span><hr size=1> Forget the PoA sword....that takes forever to quest for, Darkmetal Falchion owns it anyhow with 23/29 7 wis int SK/pally only 1hs.<br><br>But, the FD was well worth it for me, despite having to hold back from levelling for almost 2 months. <p>Tramddark Luxdeorum <BR>55th Knight of Brell <BR>Circle of the Unseen <BR>Morell-Thule server.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umarlowelawbringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Marlowe Lawbringer</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.zing.com/picture/p7948760bc8b86218d8cdfdf7a504d243/ff243fb1.jpg.thumb.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 693<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/6/01 6:06:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2922.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://a1060.g.akamai.net/f/1060/597/30minutes/www.zing.com/picture/p7948760bc8b86218d8cdfdf7a504d243/ff243fb1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Post 50 Pally and fa/fd question</span><hr size=1> While no one can really answer this question for you but you, I don't think it would make sense to me to stay 52 forever, especially if you do not have either book. As for the new PoA quest sword, the risk/reward is seriously out of whack there. It is only marginally better than an SoB (19/27, +50 mana), and I've killed the NPC that drops it with as few as five people. And both are clearly inferior to FD. <p>Marlowe Lawbringer<BR>Crusader of Mithaniel Marr, 60th Level<BR>Pseudolus Max, Godless Rogue, 35th Level<BR>Lords of Edelo, Innoruuk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrwyth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>krwyth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/6/01 8:15:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2922.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Post 50 Pally and fa/fd question</span><hr size=1> I considered this also for about 15 minutes, and then decided that grouping and leveling is way more fun than waiting around for silly dragon raids and praying for a book.<br><br>So now I'm a 55 pally who will prolly never see a fa/fd but having plenty of fun. Being a hi-elf and having a shot at nd helped this decision tho ... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uluthair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luthair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 578<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/6/01 8:49:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2922.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Post 50 Pally and fa/fd question</span><hr size=1> Darkmetal Falchion does less damage than Thelorn (PoA).<br><br>Neither compare to a 2h weapons though, not even close to FD. <p><IMG SRC="http://luthair.tripod.com/luth_sig.gif" USEMAP="#Luthair" BORDER=0></IMG><BR><IMG src="http://luthair.tripod.com/luth_beg.jpg"></img><MAP NAME="Luthair"><AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="0,0,158,21" HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=41444"></MAP></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadmandelu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adman Delu</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://members.spree.com/sip/tspaar/noel/fantasy/flame.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 552<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/6/01 9:03:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2922.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Post 50 Pally and fa/fd question</span><hr size=1> I stopped leveling 2 bubs from 53 and spent a couple months constantly doing dragons and leveling my bard. Did my own vox raid eventually to get her book. The way I saw it, after 52, I'd be 56 to 58 before I got FA (kunark dragons are hard and drop the books just as infrequent as nag/vox). I did not want to wait that long. <br><br>I think paladins (and bards) should never miss a dragon raid when at level 51/52. And hope to get a bumped roll on books, or have only 50+ paladins rolling. Talk to the raid leader before hand about this, or, learn how to lead your own nag/vox raids. <p><A HREF="mailto:damianicus@hotmail.com"><img src=http://members.aol.com/nycdamian/Montage4.jpg height=100 width=350></a><BR><BR><FONT SIZE="-1"><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=37700">54 Paladin</A> and tailor.</FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upauloaldeln.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PauloAlDeln</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/6/01 9:35:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2922.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.rochester.rr.com/jeremyfrick/images/paulo_thumb.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Post 50 Pally and fa/fd question</span><hr size=1> I feel I'm in the same spot...but I think I'm going to stay below 52...like Adman, I don't want to wait till 56 to try to get my FA, my guild just isn't big enough to do the Kunark dragons.<br><br>It sucks, but it's a decision that you have to make at some point. <p><HR WIDTH=40%><PRE>Paulo Al'Deln --<A HREF = "http://www.angler-info.com/assembly.htm">Assembly of Norrath</A>--<BR>51 Cavalier of Thunder<BR><A HREF="http://pub13.ezboard.com/btunare">Tunare</A><BR></PRE><HR WIDTH=40%></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=augie>Augie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/6/01 10:28:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2922.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Post 50 Pally and fa/fd question</span><hr size=1> I'd just like to add one more thing about FD and Nature's Defender.  FD barely makes the damage bonus for weapons with delay 40 and above.  This is crucial for us paladins to be effective taunters.  There is no way we can outdamage a warrior or a monk for cumulative damage.  Yes, you can do some good damage with a Zephyrwind or a Darkmetal Falchion, but you'll never get high enough on the hate list of the big mobs in a big drawn out fight to get it aggroed on you for even a short time.  It just won't happen.  And that's our goal, right?  To be effective taunters.  Well with a 1 hander, it aint happening.  2 handers are the key to being a good taunter.  As a fighter, it is our job to shift the damage equally to all melee members of the group.  You can't do that with a 1 handed weapon.<br><br>This is the scenario.  Warrior A uses his epic to get aggro on a mob.  Wizard B nukes the mob and gets aggro on him.  Paladin A with a 1 hander tries in vain, but FAILS to get aggro off of the wizard and on him because he can't do enough damage in the short time it takes the mob to kill the wizzie with 10hp.  Paladin B with a FD hits the mob for 200, 175 damage double attack plus Holy Shock 155DD plus stun.  Instant aggro.<br><br>Anytime a mob switches aggro, the next aggro is up for grabs.  The warrior has to build up cumulative damage again.  Paladin A will always be behind Warrior A in that category.  It is Paladin B that has a chance to save that wizards life, thereby doing his job as a taunter, simply with his weapon.  Every paladin that wields a 1 handed weapon in the planes never gets hit.  I see it all the time.<br><br>No 1 hander has a proc as awesome as FD or ND.  None of them have the great str increase.  None of them have the +10 to all resists, which in my opinion is HUGE.  Yeah, you can get a shield with some resists, but what good is that extra armor class if you're not getting hit?????  None, I say.<br><br>Let's compare a paladin with a Zephyrwind and a Shield of the Stalwart Seas to one with a FD or ND.<br><br>The 1hs pally has 35 AC.  FD pally has 15 AC.<br>The 1hs pally has bash.  FD pally has bash.<br>The 1hs pally has a 19/26 weapon.  FD pally has 35/40 sword.<br>The decimal ratio of Zephyrwind is .7 and change. FD is .8 and change  1.0 being the goal, FD has a better damage/delay ratio.<br>The 1hs pally has no proc.  FD pally has 155dd plus stun.<br>The 1hs pally has +20 str on the shield.  FD pally has the same on his sword.<br>The 1hs pally has no resists.  FD pally has +10 to all resists.<br>The 1hs pally has no wisdom, hp or mana bonus.<br>FD pally has good increases on each stat.<br><br>Even if you switch to a Sarnak Battle Shield, you're losing str and ultravision, which erudites can't even see without.  No offense to you Erudite pallys out there.  You're cool, just a little odd.  /em chuckle  I use the erudite pally example because that shield has the best AC besides the new Dracoliche one or the one that drops from Phara Dar.<br><br>I say suck up the AC hit and become a better damage dealer and be a more effective fighter.  Besides, you can still wear a Lodizal shell shield on the back, or that new one off the Dracoliche.  40AC on the back slot.<br><br>Augie-Shorty from Karana  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=augie>Augie</A> at: 4/6/01 10:37:40 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugarthintrueknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garthin Trueknight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/6/01 1:24:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.c